&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Change the way the world travels&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since 2009, GetYourGuide has been connecting travelers with the experiences they&#39;ll talk about for the rest of their lives. From skip-the-line access to iconic landmarks to once-in-a-lifetime adventures with local experts, we&#39;ve helped millions of people in over 12,000 cities discover what makes a destination truly worth visiting. Our global marketplace is home to more than 200,000 activities across 50,000 experience creators, and we&#39;re just getting started.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re building out our North America team and looking for someone who&#39;s ready to make their mark.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an Account Manager to join our Sales team in New York City. You&#39;ll own a book of business made up of mid-market supplier partners across the US and Canada, with full accountability for their performance, satisfaction, and commercial growth on our platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll build trust &amp;amp; influence with your accounts, act as their strategic partner, and find every opportunity to help them thrive. That means pitching new expansion ideas, solving problems, digging into data, and showing up for your partners in a way that makes GetYourGuide their most valuable business relationship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role for someone who&#39;s commercially sharp, genuinely curious, and excited about being part of a company that&#39;s redefining how people explore the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage and grow a book of business consisting of mid-market supplier accounts (tours, activities, and experience providers), understand your assigned market(s), and hit your performance targets&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Empower your accounts for success through education, resources, and enablement and become their go-to partner at GetYourGuide for growth and strategy to drive long-term retention&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pitch, cross-sell, and upsell to win high-velocity commercial opportunities including new activity listings, increased availability, and commission negotiations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Partner with internal teams to identify roadblocks, troubleshoot connectivity issues, and escalate tactfully to provide a world-class supplier experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Focus on operational excellence and monitor partner health by solving supplier challenges such as reducing cancellation rates, promoting on-trip quality, and increasing review scoring to foster a great customer/traveler experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Review account performance regularly, share clear insights with management, and proactively flag opportunities for expansion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your toolkit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2 to 3 years of experience in Account Management or Customer Success, ideally in tech or a marketplace environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A track record of hitting (and beating) commercial targets&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong communication skills and the ability to build trust with partners quickly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A data-driven mindset; you&#39;re comfortable working with performance metrics and turning numbers into action&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Passion for shaping the future of sales and partner success in the age of AI. You thrive in fast-paced environments, using available resources to build and scale efficiently&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great problem-solving skills and a proactive, ownership-oriented attitude&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enthusiasm for travel and genuine enthusiasm for what

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Change the way the world travels&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join the GetYourGuide journey to connect people with unforgettable travel experiences around the world. Millions look to us for unique activities they can trust, and it’s all powered by our commitment to make every single journey extraordinary - including yours.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ready to unlock your potential with a community of fellow explorers? Find your next role at our Berlin HQ or one of our local offices around the globe, from New York to Bangkok. Head to&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.getyourguide.careers/&quot;&gt;getyourguide.careers&lt;/a&gt; to take the first step.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI adoption at GetYourGuide is growing fast, and the decisions made now — about what we build, what we allow, and how we govern it — will shape the company for years. This is a high-visibility, cross-functional role that sits at the intersection of AI strategy, security, legal, and product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work directly with the AI Council, IT, Security, and Legal, and partner with AI-focused teams across the business. The role reports into SaaS Operations and operates with company-wide scope: you will build and operate the technical foundations for AI adoption, execute against the governance framework and strategic direction set by IT leadership, and be the go-to technical owner for putting AI governance into practice day to day..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bring GetYourGuide&#39;s internal AI governance framework to life, from policy into practice. This means:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build and operate the technical foundations&lt;/strong&gt; that put the &lt;strong&gt;AI governance framework into practice&lt;/strong&gt;: implement the standards, guardrails, and tooling that determine how AI tools are evaluated, adopted, and used across the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execute against the AI enablement roadmap&lt;/strong&gt;, balancing innovation velocity with security, compliance, and operational integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the &lt;strong&gt;primary technical point of contact internally&lt;/strong&gt;, the go-to advisor for teams navigating tooling choices and shadow AI risks, escalating governance calls to IT leadership when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support cross-functional alignment between AI, Security, Legal, and business stakeholders&lt;/strong&gt;, translating technical trade-offs into clear recommendations for decision makers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the &lt;strong&gt;reduction of shadow AI and fragmentation across the organization&lt;/strong&gt; through governance structures that are practical enough to actually get adopted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Evaluate AI platforms and tools and recommend selections&lt;/strong&gt; based on security posture, compliance requirements, and long-term operational fit, not just near-term capability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your toolkit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Enablement and Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of implementing AI governance frameworks, tooling, or enablement programs at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical judgment on where to move fast and where to slow down when rolling out AI capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional Influence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience operating at the intersection of technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to challenge assumptions, surface the real problem behind a request, and guide decisions under ambiguity without waiting for permission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
